mages</figcaption></figure><p>这些利润很可能得益于流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-new-premium-price-hike-for-the-us-3762105">在 2024 年 6 月上旬提高了大部分现有计划的价格。</a>此外， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announces-cut-of-1500-jobs-with-17-per-cent-of-workforce-facing-axe-3552871">Spotify 决定在 2023 年底削减 17% 的员工以节省成本，</a>这可能也有助于他们的利润增加。这一决定是在之前实施的一项计划之后做出的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-to-cut-six-per-cent-of-workforce-3385265">，该计划旨在于 2023 年初再裁员 6%，</a>以提高“速度”。</p><p>除了价格上涨和员工的裁员外，利润也可能受益于流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-has-now-officially-demonetised-all-songs-with-less-than-1000-streams-3614010">正式将平台上的所有歌曲宣传不到1,000流</a>。</p><p>该政策于4月1日启动，但<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-confirm-songs-now-need-at-least-1000-streams-to-earn-royalties-3546548">已由该平台计划了一段时间</a>。很快就批评了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">艺术家很难从音乐中获得特许权使用费，并限制了希望破解音乐行业的新艺术家</a>。</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kate-nash">凯特·纳什（Kate Nash）</a>最近在她的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kate-nash-and-her-bum-on-the-back-of-a-fire-truck-take-to-livenation-offices-to-protest-3816821">“消防车后部的流浪汉”抗议活动中强调了低流的特许权使用费，在那里她前往Spotify的伦敦办公室</a>，并通过版权代码说：取消了平台上80％的音乐。股东之间兑现了超过4.19亿。”</p><p>最近， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-unwrapped-parody-site-taken-down-under-legal-threat-after-claiming-what-artists-really-earned-from-streams-in-2024-3819279">应Spotify的法律团队的要求取消了一个模仿Spotify包裹的网站。</a>该网站的标题为“ <a href="https://www.spotifyunwrapped.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spotify拆开</a>”，强调了低薪艺术家从该平台收到的。 </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/C_YCjHmRloO/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,